                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote>
                        <p>facia running along the top of the base insiced with an egg-and-dart motif; front face of the base decorated with incised frontal busts of the moon (right), with two horns projecting from her head, and the sun (left), with his radiate crown; six irregulary spaced rosettes around the field, and an egg-and-dart motif along the vertical edges; back and left faces are plain; right face bears a punctate inscription in Greek; omphalos is decorated with a net pattern of triple incised lines, intended for fillets, with rosettes in between; roughly crescent-shaped broken area on top of the omphalos indicates where Victory once stood; the edges of the break are jagged, with a small ridge of bronze along the left rear edge; placement of the feet is apparent at each end of the break: proper left foot of Victory was set lower than the right and was slightly advanced</p>
                     </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
